description: Strict release shipping — patch + full packages, docs, push, cleanup
alwaysApply: true
---

# Release shipping (mandatory)

On every shipped version in Hangup HR:

1. **Bump** `package.json` version; update all relevant MD docs (`CHANGELOG.md`, `README.md`, `AI_Agent.md`, `FEATURES.md`, `TUTORIAL.md`, `UPDATES.md`, `SALES_LOG.md` when applicable).

2. **Commit and push** to GitHub before triggering CI — never run Release workflow until `git push` completes.

3. **GitHub release must include BOTH:**
   - **Patch zips** — `Hangup-Portal-{version}-{platform}-patch-from-{prev}.zip` (when prior manifest exists)
   - **Full packages** — `Hangup-Portal-Setup-{version}.exe`, `{version}-win-x64-full.zip`, mac full zips + DMG
   - **Web installer** — `Hangup-Portal-Web-Setup.exe` (pinned to `package.json` version)
   - **Manifests** — `win-x64-latest.json`, `mac-*-latest.json`

4. **After CI:** promote release to Latest; remove stale assets from the release (wrong version duplicates); run `node scripts/publish-app-version.js`.

5. **Web installer:** rebuild with `npm run dist:web-installer` (defaults to package.json pin). `PickBestSetupAsset` must match release tag version, not an older Setup.exe on the same release.

6. **Do not commit** deleted CSVs, log files, or `.env`.

```powershell
git push origin HEAD
# wait for push
gh workflow run "Release (update packages)" --repo raymondwalkerhs-spec/hangup-hr --ref desktop/1.0.8-beta.1-updates -f tag=vX.Y.Z
gh run watch --repo raymondwalkerhs-spec/hangup-hr
gh release edit vX.Y.Z --repo raymondwalkerhs-spec/hangup-hr --prerelease=false --latest
```
